WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.896 --> 00:00:15.271
Hello?

2
00:00:15.438 --> 00:00:17.354
Hello.
Uh. yes?

3
00:00:17.521 --> 00:00:18.646
Who is this?

4
00:00:18.813 --> 00:00:21.396
Who are you calling?
Who am I speaking to?

5
00:00:21.563 --> 00:00:23.063
Wrong number.

6
00:00:23.229 --> 00:00:25.438
Who was that?
Oh. nobody.

7
00:00:25.604 --> 00:00:27.021
Did you pick a movie?

8
00:00:27.188 --> 00:00:29.979
Yeah. We're gonna go scary.
Saw IV.

9
00:00:30.146 --> 00:00:32.396
Ugh. I saw that in theatres. It sucks.

10
00:00:32.563 --> 00:00:35.521
It's not scary. it's gross.
I hate all that torture porn shit.

11
00:00:35.688 --> 00:00:37.646
How do you really feel?

12
00:00:38.771 --> 00:00:42.521
Well. I like Jigsaw.
I think he kills people very creatively.

13
00:00:42.688 --> 00:00:45.896
<i>But you don't give a shit who dies
'cause there's no character development.</i>

14
00:00:46.063 --> 00:00:48.771
<i>There's just body parts ripping
and blood spewing. Blah.</i>

15
00:00:48.938 --> 00:00:50.521
Who do you keep texting?

16
00:00:50.688 --> 00:00:53.479
I have a Facebook stalker.
He keeps leaving me messages.

17
00:00:53.646 --> 00:00:56.229
Yeah. like what?
Just stuff.

18
00:00:56.396 --> 00:00:58.771
Like. “Hey. what's up?
You're hot. I wanna kill you.”

19
00:00:58.938 --> 00:01:00.563
So delete him.

20
00:01:00.729 --> 00:01:03.146
I did. but he hacked his way back in.

21
00:01:03.313 --> 00:01:05.479
So report him.

22
00:01:05.646 --> 00:01:08.063
He's really hot. though.

23
00:01:08.229 --> 00:01:10.063
You wanna see?

24
00:01:13.604 --> 00:01:15.271
That's Channing Tatum.

25
00:01:15.438 --> 00:01:18.021
It is not. Is it?

26
00:01:18.188 --> 00:01:19.646
Yeah. from his Abercrombie days.

27
00:01:19.813 --> 00:01:21.313
You are being punked.

28
00:01:28.354 --> 00:01:30.563
- Hello?
- Who is this?

29
00:01:30.729 --> 00:01:33.521
The more impatient version of
the person you just spoke to.

30
00:01:33.688 --> 00:01:36.354
I'm sorry. You don't
have to be a bitch about it.

31
00:01:36.521 --> 00:01:37.896
No. of course I don't. Eat me.

32
00:01:38.063 --> 00:01:41.146
You hang up on me and I'll cut through
your neck until I feel bone!

33
00:01:41.313 --> 00:01:44.188
Who is it?
It's for you.

34
00:01:46.521 --> 00:01:47.396
Hello?

35
00:01:47.563 --> 00:01:48.938
Who's this?

36
00:01:49.104 --> 00:01:51.146
It's Trudie. Who's this?

37
00:01:51.313 --> 00:01:54.688
This is the last person
you're ever gonna see alive.

38
00:01:54.854 --> 00:01:56.438
It's a prank. Hang up.

39
00:01:56.604 --> 00:01:59.854
Why'd you hand the phone to me?
You're the one with the stalker.

40
00:02:00.021 --> 00:02:01.938
Are the doors locked?

41
00:02:02.104 --> 00:02:03.688
Don't freak out.

42
00:02:07.896 --> 00:02:09.688
Let it ring.

43
00:02:16.271 --> 00:02:19.354
It's from stalker boy.

44
00:02:19.521 --> 00:02:21.354
He said. “Answer the phone.”

45
00:02:21.521 --> 00:02:24.396
For God's sake.
It's a joke. Trudie.

46
00:02:24.563 --> 00:02:26.563
It's probably Lexi or Karen.
Where are you going?

47
00:02:26.729 --> 00:02:28.688
To make sure the front door is locked.

48
00:02:31.438 --> 00:02:33.104
<i>No. Don't open it.</i>

49
00:02:33.271 --> 00:02:34.813
You're overreacting.

50
00:02:37.063 --> 00:02:39.438
It's a joke. Trudie. OK?

51
00:02:39.604 --> 00:02:41.979
Somebody made a dummy profile.
They're just trying to scare you.

52
00:02:42.146 --> 00:02:45.104
Wait. Who is it?

53
00:02:45.271 --> 00:02:48.229
I said. who is it?

54
00:02:49.354 --> 00:02:50.729
Let's call the cops.

55
00:02:54.771 --> 00:02:56.396
“I dare you to open the door.”

56
00:02:56.563 --> 00:02:58.104
No. Sherrie. Don't.

57
00:02:58.271 --> 00:02:59.896
No. don't. I'm scared.

58
00:03:00.063 --> 00:03:02.354
Hey. it could be anyone that we know.

59
00:03:02.521 --> 00:03:06.854
Lisa. Bailey. Wayne — or the hopeful
long shot. Channing Tatum.

60
00:03:24.521 --> 00:03:26.396
There's nobody out here.

61
00:03:30.854 --> 00:03:32.521
What does it say?

62
00:03:32.688 --> 00:03:36.313
It says. “I'm not outside.
I'm right beside you.”

63
00:03:39.563 --> 00:03:41.688
Trudie! Tru...

64
00:03:41.854 --> 00:03:42.729
Oh. my God!

65
00:04:00.188 --> 00:04:02.271
Fucking kidding me.

66
00:04:02.438 --> 00:04:03.813
What?

67
00:04:03.979 --> 00:04:05.354
That was so fucking stupid.

68
00:04:05.521 --> 00:04:08.313
Pure horseshit. The death of horror
right here in front of us.

69
00:04:08.479 --> 00:04:10.021
I jumped. It scared me.

70
00:04:10.188 --> 00:04:12.979
A fucking Facebook killer?
You're kidding me. right?

71
00:04:13.146 --> 00:04:15.396
I guess now it would be Twitter.

72
00:04:15.563 --> 00:04:16.938
That'd make more sense.

73
00:04:17.104 --> 00:04:21.063
A bunch of articulate teens sit around
and deconstruct horror movies

74
00:04:21.229 --> 00:04:23.854
until Ghostface kills them one by one?

75
00:04:24.021 --> 00:04:28.604
It's been done to death. the whole
self-aware. postmodern. meta shit.

76
00:04:28.771 --> 00:04:31.438
Stick a fork in 1996 already.

77
00:04:31.604 --> 00:04:33.854
I like the 'Stab' movies.

78
00:04:34.021 --> 00:04:35.396
They're scarier.

79
00:04:35.563 --> 00:04:38.771
It's not aliens or zombies
or little Asian ghost girls.

80
00:04:38.938 --> 00:04:41.979
There's something real
about a guy with a knife who just...

81
00:04:43.188 --> 00:04:44.854
<i>...snaps.</i>

82
00:04:46.438 --> 00:04:48.188
It could really happen.

83
00:04:48.354 --> 00:04:50.479
I can't do it.

84
00:04:50.646 --> 00:04:52.021
These sequels don't know when to stop.

85
00:04:52.188 --> 00:04:54.438
They just keep recycling the same shit.

86
00:04:54.604 --> 00:04:57.438
Even the opening scene —
there's always some random girl

87
00:04:57.604 --> 00:04:59.771
who gets a call that undoubtedly
ends up getting her killed.

88
00:04:59.938 --> 00:05:02.229
It's all so predictable.
There's no element of surprise.

89
00:05:02.396 --> 00:05:04.896
You can see everything coming.

90
00:05:10.521 --> 00:05:12.188
Did that surprise you?

91
00:05:14.521 --> 00:05:16.104
It's your own fault.

92
00:05:16.271 --> 00:05:17.938
Why?

93
00:05:18.104 --> 00:05:19.563
Because you talk too much.

94
00:05:21.479 --> 00:05:24.729
Now shut the fuck up
and watch the movie.

95
00:05:32.729 --> 00:05:37.396
Oh. my God. I love it. I've seen it five times
and it still gets me every time.

96
00:05:37.563 --> 00:05:40.146
You're kidding. I don't get it.

97
00:05:42.729 --> 00:05:46.646
OK. It's like 'The Twilight Zone"...
'“Twilight Zone'?

98
00:05:46.813 --> 00:05:49.563
A movie within a movie.
I get that. But it's illogical.

99
00:05:49.729 --> 00:05:52.521
It begs the question that if
the beginning of 'Stab 7' is 'Stab 6.

100
00:05:52.688 --> 00:05:54.563
<i>then is the beginning of 'Stab &'
'Stab 57?</i>

101
00:05:54.729 --> 00:05:56.271
And if so. what is 'Stab 4' about?

102
00:05:56.438 --> 00:05:57.813
You're overthinking it.

103
00:05:57.979 --> 00:06:00.688
Am I? Or did whoever made it
just under think it?

104
00:06:00.854 --> 00:06:02.563
There's a reason
I don't watch these movies.

105
00:06:02.729 --> 00:06:06.021
I can't believe you haven't seen them.
We live in Woodsboro.

106
00:06:06.188 --> 00:06:08.521
That has nothing to do with Woodsboro.

107
00:06:08.688 --> 00:06:11.479
I thought you said 'Stab'
was based on true stories.

108
00:06:11.646 --> 00:06:15.104
The first three — the original trilogy —
is based off of Sidney Prescott.

109
00:06:15.271 --> 00:06:17.896
But then she threatened to sue them
if they used her story.

110
00:06:18.063 --> 00:06:19.563
so then they just started making stuff up.

111
00:06:19.729 --> 00:06:22.938
'Stab 5' has time travel.
which is by far the worst.

112
00:06:23.104 --> 00:06:25.604
Don't we hear enough
about this story every year?

113
00:06:25.771 --> 00:06:29.021
At least Woodsboro's
known for something.

114
00:06:30.771 --> 00:06:31.646
Did you hear that?

115
00:06:31.813 --> 00:06:35.396
Uh... no. I didn't hear anything.

116
00:06:35.563 --> 00:06:37.771
I did.

117
00:06:39.438 --> 00:06:41.271
Jenny. don't try to scare me.

118
00:06:41.438 --> 00:06:43.813
I'm not trying to scare you.
You do it all the time.

119
00:06:43.979 --> 00:06:46.271
No. I don't.
Where are you going?

120
00:06:46.438 --> 00:06:48.313
I told you — I heard something.

121
00:06:48.479 --> 00:06:49.854
I know you're trying to scare me.

122
00:06:50.021 --> 00:06:52.313
I'm not.

123
00:06:58.729 --> 00:06:59.979
What is it?

124
00:07:01.229 --> 00:07:03.854
I must have left
a window in my room open.

125
00:07:06.813 --> 00:07:08.521
Could you get that?

126
00:07:08.688 --> 00:07:11.313
Marnie?
Yeah.

127
00:07:15.771 --> 00:07:17.146
Hello?

128
00:07:17.313 --> 00:07:19.104
Hello. Who is this?

129
00:07:19.271 --> 00:07:21.646
Marnie. Who's this?

130
00:07:21.813 --> 00:07:26.021
This is the last person
you're ever gonna see alive.

131
00:07:27.979 --> 00:07:29.604
What?

132
00:07:32.271 --> 00:07:33.146
I'm sorry.

133
00:07:33.313 --> 00:07:34.688
I had to.

134
00:07:34.854 --> 00:07:37.021
You bitch!

135
00:07:37.188 --> 00:07:38.938
So not funny.

136
00:07:39.104 --> 00:07:41.313
Somebody falls for it every year.

137
00:07:41.479 --> 00:07:43.313
I don't see why you get off on this...

138
00:07:45.313 --> 00:07:46.479
Marnie?

139
00:07:49.104 --> 00:07:50.729
Marnie?

140
00:07:53.938 --> 00:07:55.479
Marnie?

141
00:08:02.313 --> 00:08:03.688
Good one. Marnie.

142
00:08:03.854 --> 00:08:05.521
Lights out. phone on the floor.

143
00:08:05.688 --> 00:08:09.563
You know. you really should
direct horror films...

144
00:08:09.729 --> 00:08:12.104
...wherever you are.

145
00:08:14.563 --> 00:08:15.938
Let me guess...

146
00:08:16.104 --> 00:08:20.104
you want me to walk by an open door
frame so you can pop out. huh?

147
00:08:24.938 --> 00:08:27.938
OK. timing — timing is perfect.

148
00:08:28.104 --> 00:08:31.229
But you don't have
the app on your phone.

149
00:08:31.396 --> 00:08:34.146
so you can't talk
like Ghostface. can you?

150
00:08:34.313 --> 00:08:35.896
Yes. I can.

151
00:08:36.063 --> 00:08:37.771
Who is this?

152
00:08:37.938 --> 00:08:39.313
Not an app.

153
00:08:39.479 --> 00:08:40.854
Is this Trevor?

154
00:08:41.021 --> 00:08:42.521
Do I sound like a Trevor to you?

155
00:08:42.688 --> 00:08:44.146
Think of me as your director.

156
00:08:44.313 --> 00:08:47.479
You're in my movie. You've got
a fun part. so don't blow it.

157
00:08:47.646 --> 00:08:48.521
What movie?

158
00:08:48.688 --> 00:08:52.646
Same one Marnie's in.
only her part got cut way back.

159
00:08:52.813 --> 00:08:55.771
But you — you're the dumb blonde
with the big tits.

160
00:08:55.938 --> 00:08:58.646
We'll have some fun with you
before you die.

161
00:08:58.813 --> 00:09:02.521
I have a 4.0 GPA and 1351Q. asshole.

162
00:09:02.688 --> 00:09:04.188
What did you do with Marnie?

163
00:09:04.354 --> 00:09:05.896
She's on the cutting-room floor.

164
00:09:06.063 --> 00:09:08.896
That's not funny.
This isn't a comedy. It's a horror film.

165
00:09:09.063 --> 00:09:10.479
People live. people die.

166
00:09:10.646 --> 00:09:12.271
And you'd better start running.

167
00:09:17.396 --> 00:09:18.979
Marnie?

168
00:10:55.646 --> 00:10:58.771
J Working for another hour tonight

169
00:10:58.938 --> 00:11:02.396
♪ Staring at the wall
and let the time just pass me by

170
00:11:02.563 --> 00:11:05.854
♪ You might think you know me
but it's all just a face

171
00:11:06.021 --> 00:11:09.229
♪ Trying to ignore when people screaming
my name

172
00:11:09.396 --> 00:11:14.521
J When something's right.
then something is worth to die for

173
00:11:14.688 --> 00:11:21.604
J When I feel that something is wrong.
then something is worth to fight for

174
00:11:21.771 --> 00:11:24.896
J Don't say goodbye

175
00:11:25.063 --> 00:11:28.646
♪ Just leave an open door

176
00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:31.896
J I wanna hear you say

177
00:11:32.063 --> 00:11:36.104
J You give me something to die for... J

178
00:11:37.563 --> 00:11:38.938
What do you think?

179
00:11:39.104 --> 00:11:40.604
Well. I guess today is the anniversary.

180
00:11:40.771 --> 00:11:42.396
Kids.

181
00:11:42.563 --> 00:11:43.938
No. I meant the display.

182
00:11:44.104 --> 00:11:45.688
Oh!

183
00:11:50.563 --> 00:11:51.938
It's good!

184
00:11:52.104 --> 00:11:54.854
I told the owner I'd kill his cat
if he didn't get it right.

185
00:11:55.021 --> 00:11:57.146
Nice!

186
00:12:38.021 --> 00:12:39.688
Ho! Whoa. whoa. whoa!

187
00:12:39.854 --> 00:12:41.229
25. stay alive!

188
00:12:41.396 --> 00:12:44.313
Shit! Sorry. Sheriff!

189
00:12:45.979 --> 00:12:47.354
Kirby.

190
00:12:50.146 --> 00:12:51.688
Phew!

191
00:13:03.813 --> 00:13:06.813
Hey. before you get in the car.
you have to promise not to kill me.

192
00:13:06.979 --> 00:13:08.938
Why? What did you do?

193
00:13:09.104 --> 00:13:11.729
Trevor called me last night.
Why is he calling you?

194
00:13:11.896 --> 00:13:14.563
Because you won't take his calls.
he knows I have your ear.

195
00:13:14.729 --> 00:13:16.104
and he wants to know.

196
00:13:16.271 --> 00:13:18.979
Know what?
How upset you are.

197
00:13:20.396 --> 00:13:22.146
Can we just not talk about this. please?
Fine.

198
00:13:22.313 --> 00:13:25.729
OK. so Trevor called me last night.

199
00:13:25.896 --> 00:13:27.313
He called you too?

200
00:13:27.479 --> 00:13:29.146
He's worried your cousin
coming to Woodsboro

201
00:13:29.313 --> 00:13:31.729
is distracting you from knowing
how sorry he really is.

202
00:13:31.896 --> 00:13:34.438
Well. that's inventive.
Oh. God!

203
00:13:36.438 --> 00:13:39.188
Problem with Trevor is he never quits.

204
00:13:39.354 --> 00:13:42.438
By the way. have you seen
the Grim Reaper? Angel of Death?

205
00:13:42.604 --> 00:13:44.438
What are you talking about?

206
00:13:44.604 --> 00:13:46.271
Your cousin.
Sidney.

207
00:13:46.438 --> 00:13:50.229
Last stop on her book tour.
first stop on her road to a new life.

208
00:13:50.396 --> 00:13:51.771
It's very dramatic.

209
00:13:51.938 --> 00:13:54.104
She's the reason why
I love horror movies.

210
00:13:54.271 --> 00:13:56.271
I"m sure she'd love to hear that.

211
00:13:56.438 --> 00:13:58.646
if I knew her — which I don't. really.

212
00:13:58.813 --> 00:14:02.354
Wherever she went. people died.
Other people.

213
00:14:02.521 --> 00:14:03.896
It was never her.

214
00:14:04.063 --> 00:14:07.021
I mean. 'Stab' is the wrong franchise
for her. It should be 'Final Destination'.

215
00:14:08.729 --> 00:14:11.229
OK. why is Jenny Randall calling me?
Ooh. the other woman.

216
00:14:11.396 --> 00:14:12.813
- Hello?
- Hello. Jill.

217
00:14:12.979 --> 00:14:14.521
I can't stand Jenn...
Shh!

218
00:14:14.688 --> 00:14:16.063
Jenny. is this you?

219
00:14:16.229 --> 00:14:19.146
What's your favourite scary movie?

220
00:14:19.313 --> 00:14:20.688
OK. who is this?

221
00:14:20.854 --> 00:14:22.438
What does she want?

222
00:14:23.479 --> 00:14:25.271
I said. “Who is this?”

223
00:14:25.438 --> 00:14:27.313
I asked you a question.

224
00:14:27.479 --> 00:14:30.896
What's your favourite scary movie?

225
00:14:31.063 --> 00:14:32.438
I'm hanging up.

226
00:14:33.771 --> 00:14:36.688
Wow. That was original.

227
00:14:36.854 --> 00:14:40.188
I got a call like that this morning
from Marnie the Carny.

228
00:14:40.354 --> 00:14:41.396
What?

229
00:14:41.563 --> 00:14:42.646
Watch out!

230
00:14:44.563 --> 00:14:46.396
Nice move. asshole!

231
00:14:46.563 --> 00:14:48.896
You just ran a stop sign.

232
00:14:49.063 --> 00:14:51.479
Sorry.

233
00:14:53.771 --> 00:14:55.438
Angel of Death!

234
00:15:01.313 --> 00:15:03.354
The mayor wants these down
before lunch.

235
00:15:03.521 --> 00:15:05.104
Only 25 more to go.

236
00:15:08.771 --> 00:15:10.229
Morning. Sheriff.

237
00:15:10.396 --> 00:15:13.229
Morning. Deputy. Joe.
Morning. Sheriff.

238
00:15:13.396 --> 00:15:16.354
Looks like the celebration's begun.

239
00:15:16.521 --> 00:15:18.604
High school kids. probably.

240
00:15:18.771 --> 00:15:22.604
Yeah. One generation's tragedy
is the next one's joke.

241
00:15:22.771 --> 00:15:25.104
Sorry you can never get away from this.

242
00:15:25.271 --> 00:15:28.938
You know. I wish I'd been old enough
to be a part of the force

243
00:15:29.104 --> 00:15:30.521
when you were solving those crimes.

244
00:15:30.688 --> 00:15:32.063
Why's that?

245
00:15:32.229 --> 00:15:35.938
It's those intense investigations
that really bond relationships.

246
00:15:37.021 --> 00:15:38.854
Uh. yeah.

247
00:15:39.021 --> 00:15:40.688
How is Gale. by the way?

248
00:15:40.854 --> 00:15:43.271
Gale's good. She's writing.

249
00:15:43.438 --> 00:15:45.563
Fiction.

250
00:15:45.729 --> 00:15:47.104
Or trying.

251
00:15:47.271 --> 00:15:49.271
Hey. I made some lemon squares.
They're in my car.

252
00:15:49.438 --> 00:15:52.938
Oh. thanks. Deputy. but no. thanks.

253
00:15:53.104 --> 00:15:57.188
Sheriff! You're not cheating on your wife
if you eat my lemon square.

254
00:15:57.354 --> 00:16:00.021
Yeah. but I would be
cheating on my diet.

255
00:16:01.729 --> 00:16:03.563
Sheriff Riley!
Come in. Sheriff Riley.

256
00:16:03.729 --> 00:16:05.313
This is Sheriff Riley. Go ahead.

257
00:16:05.479 --> 00:16:07.396
You gotta get over to
the Randall house right away.

258
00:16:07.563 --> 00:16:09.813
It's bad. Sheriff. Real bad.

259
00:16:21.479 --> 00:16:23.604
The book is 'Out of Darkness'.

260
00:16:23.771 --> 00:16:26.104
and its author. Sidney Prescott.
is here with us today.

261
00:16:26.271 --> 00:16:30.188
Have the seven 'Stab' movies. all based
on Gale Weathers's books about you.

262
00:16:30.354 --> 00:16:32.813
made it even harder to go on?

263
00:16:32.979 --> 00:16:35.688
I don't blame Gale. That's in the past.

264
00:16:35.854 --> 00:16:40.646
No. if I was a victim for too long.
it was up to me to reinvent myself.

265
00:16:40.813 --> 00:16:42.313
That's why I wrote this book.

266
00:16:42.479 --> 00:16:46.938
<i>Sidney Prescott. everybody. And rave reviews
for her book. 'Out of Darkness'.</i>

267
00:16:47.104 --> 00:16:49.604
Alright. Gale. Let's do it.

268
00:16:49.771 --> 00:16:51.729
Let's reinvent myself.

269
00:16:51.896 --> 00:16:55.063
Except...

270
00:16:56.938 --> 00:17:02.938
<i>“I.. Have... no fucking idea
what to.. Write”</i>

271
00:17:13.604 --> 00:17:14.979
Is that new?

272
00:17:15.146 --> 00:17:17.938
That's the 2.0 upgrade version.
I'm totally mobile. man.

273
00:17:18.104 --> 00:17:20.063
Nice! Look.

274
00:17:20.229 --> 00:17:22.813
Oh! This is 'Hall Pass'
with Robbie Mercer.

275
00:17:22.979 --> 00:17:26.146
here with the luscious Olivia
“'Don't look at my tits. I have a mind” Morris.

276
00:17:26.313 --> 00:17:29.271
Here is my Woodsboro Massacre
anniversary question.

277
00:17:29.438 --> 00:17:31.438
What is your favourite scary movie?

278
00:17:31.604 --> 00:17:33.729
Is that all you got?
Some stupid douche question?

279
00:17:33.896 --> 00:17:35.729
Yeah. where'd you hear that. anyways?

280
00:17:35.896 --> 00:17:37.521
It's a line from 'Stab 1'. duh.

281
00:17:37.688 --> 00:17:39.063
Hey. Charlie.

282
00:17:39.229 --> 00:17:41.271
You're a genre nut. Kirby.
What's your favourite scary movie?

283
00:17:41.438 --> 00:17:42.854
'Bambi'.

284
00:17:43.021 --> 00:17:44.729
Mm-hm.
Dork.

285
00:17:44.896 --> 00:17:47.104
What?
That's funny. Kirby!

286
00:17:48.979 --> 00:17:51.271
Completely unaware you exist.

287
00:17:51.438 --> 00:17:53.063
No. man. she wants me.

288
00:17:55.396 --> 00:17:58.229
Yeah. I wish. right. asshole?

289
00:17:58.396 --> 00:18:00.188
I think Charlie likes you.

290
00:18:00.354 --> 00:18:05.438
And I like him — to tease. to torment.
to make him squirm.

291
00:18:05.604 --> 00:18:07.854
You could do a lot worse. trust me.

292
00:18:09.854 --> 00:18:10.729
Oh!

293
00:18:10.896 --> 00:18:13.896
Hi. Trevor. 'Bye. Trevor.

294
00:18:14.063 --> 00:18:15.688
Can we talk?

295
00:18:17.063 --> 00:18:19.563
Somebody cares about you
over here. you know!

296
00:18:19.729 --> 00:18:22.563
Someone who made you
really happy once.

297
00:18:22.729 --> 00:18:24.896
Someone who never
should have let you go.

298
00:18:25.063 --> 00:18:28.813
When you're done with a phone call.
you let someone go

299
00:18:28.979 --> 00:18:31.896
or when you take someone
to the airport. you let them go.

300
00:18:32.063 --> 00:18:34.979
But when you tell someone you love her
and she gives you everything.

301
00:18:35.146 --> 00:18:36.896
and then you just go out
with someone else.

302
00:18:37.063 --> 00:18:39.188
that is not 'letting her go'.
that"s dumping her. OK?

303
00:18:39.354 --> 00:18:41.521
That's... that's betrayal.

304
00:18:41.688 --> 00:18:45.396
Trevor Sheldon. denied.

305
00:18:45.563 --> 00:18:46.979
live on 'Hall Pass' with Robbie Mercer.

306
00:18:47.146 --> 00:18:48.979
What is your favourite
scary movie. man?

307
00:18:49.146 --> 00:18:50.313
I'll show you.

308
00:18:57.688 --> 00:19:02.229
And I began to believe myself
that that was all I was — a victim.

309
00:19:02.396 --> 00:19:04.813
And that was unacceptable to me.

310
00:19:04.979 --> 00:19:08.729
So I sat down

311
00:19:08.896 --> 00:19:11.313
and began to write a new role

312
00:19:11.479 --> 00:19:12.854
that would be my own...

313
00:19:13.021 --> 00:19:16.063
a role for a woman who could
leave the walls of fear behind

314
00:19:16.229 --> 00:19:17.813
and step out into the sunlight...

315
00:19:17.979 --> 00:19:19.354
out of darkness.

316
00:19:21.188 --> 00:19:22.646
Thank you.

317
00:19:22.813 --> 00:19:25.813
OK! We're gonna
start the book signing in a sec.

318
00:19:25.979 --> 00:19:28.354
so buy your copies while they last!

319
00:19:28.521 --> 00:19:31.354
I'm looking at you. ladies!
'New York Times' bestseller.

320
00:19:31.521 --> 00:19:33.813
Rave reviews.

321
00:19:33.979 --> 00:19:35.104
Gale.

322
00:19:35.271 --> 00:19:36.813
I'm glad you came.

323
00:19:36.979 --> 00:19:40.104
Congratulations. Sidney. I haven't
had a chance to read it yet. but...

324
00:19:40.271 --> 00:19:42.688
I know where you can get one.

325
00:19:45.354 --> 00:19:48.021
Dewey! Hey!

326
00:19:48.188 --> 00:19:51.979
Hey. Sid. Gale. you made it.
What are you doing here?

327
00:19:52.146 --> 00:19:54.563
Sid. I'm sorry. I gotta do something.

328
00:19:54.729 --> 00:19:57.063
I'm really sorry. Excuse me!

329
00:19:57.229 --> 00:19:58.646
This will only take a minute.

330
00:19:58.813 --> 00:20:01.479
I need you all to stay where you are
and remain silent.

331
00:20:01.646 --> 00:20:04.063
Nobody leaves yet.
The sheriff thanks you.

332
00:20:04.229 --> 00:20:06.146
Can this wait. Barney Fife?
I'm running an event here!

333
00:20:06.313 --> 00:20:08.104
Ma'am. this is a police event now.

334
00:20:08.271 --> 00:20:10.229
What's going on?
Gale. this is police business.

335
00:20:10.396 --> 00:20:11.896
If you could just let us handle this.

336
00:20:12.063 --> 00:20:14.438
I'm talking to my husband. Deputy Judy.

337
00:20:14.604 --> 00:20:15.979
Listen. there's a phone we believe

338
00:20:16.146 --> 00:20:18.479
may have been taken
from the scene of a crime.

339
00:20:18.646 --> 00:20:22.063
Deputy Hicks has traced its location back
to these coordinates.

340
00:20:22.229 --> 00:20:24.479
The rest is need-to-know.

341
00:20:24.646 --> 00:20:26.479
< I'm not need-to-know??

342
00:20:28.271 --> 00:20:30.521
Boss. I'm hearing something.

343
00:20:30.688 --> 00:20:32.729
Sheriff. it's ringing out here!

344
00:20:36.479 --> 00:20:37.771
There.

345
00:20:43.396 --> 00:20:44.771
It's coming from the trunk.

346
00:20:44.938 --> 00:20:46.229
Dewey.

347
00:20:46.396 --> 00:20:48.896
Gonna need everyone to stay back.
Not now. Sid.

348
00:20:49.063 --> 00:20:50.563
It's my rental.

349
00:20:59.563 --> 00:21:00.938
Damn!

350
00:21:01.104 --> 00:21:03.479
OK. it's now an official crime scene.
Let's lock it down.

351
00:21:03.646 --> 00:21:06.896
Get that camera out of here!
Everybody back.

352
00:21:07.063 --> 00:21:08.979
Please tell me this is a prank. Dewey.

353
00:21:09.146 --> 00:21:11.521
I'm afraid not. Sid.

354
00:21:11.688 --> 00:21:12.938
Come on.

355
00:21:14.521 --> 00:21:16.396
Henry. you're not gonna believe
what just happened.

356
00:21:16.563 --> 00:21:19.479
Stand back. Gale. Gale!
I just wanna see.

357
00:21:19.646 --> 00:21:21.188
Cover up your kid's eyes!

358
00:21:22.563 --> 00:21:24.854
OK. essays are due Tuesday.

359
00:21:25.021 --> 00:21:26.396
Why Woodsboro is the best...

360
00:21:27.771 --> 00:21:31.854
Anything with an on/off switch
should be off — that's the rule.

361
00:21:32.021 --> 00:21:34.313
Somebody wanna share?

362
00:21:34.479 --> 00:21:36.938
Jenny Randall and Marnie Cooper
were murdered last night.

363
00:21:37.104 --> 00:21:38.479
- What?
- Jenny and Marnie?

364
00:21:38.646 --> 00:21:40.563
What?
Stabbed to death.

365
00:21:40.729 --> 00:21:43.313
- What's your favourite scary mo...
- Shut up!

366
00:21:43.479 --> 00:21:45.979
- Yo. it's a news van!
- Class is not over.

367
00:21:46.146 --> 00:21:47.521
That was fast.

368
00:21:47.688 --> 00:21:51.271
This week marks the anniversary
of the infamous Woodsboro Murders.

369
00:21:51.438 --> 00:21:56.188
Two girls killed the exact day
local celebrity victim Sidney Prescott

370
00:21:56.354 --> 00:21:58.354
chose to return to her home town.

371
00:21:58.521 --> 00:22:00.979
It could all be something right out of
a Gale Weathers bestseller.

372
00:22:01.146 --> 00:22:04.396
And where is she now?
Well. living right here in Woodsboro...

373
00:22:04.563 --> 00:22:06.313
Mrs Riley...
Hoss.

374
00:22:06.479 --> 00:22:08.688
First lady!
Perkins!

375
00:22:09.938 --> 00:22:11.813
Excuse me. Gale.
He's conducting an interview.

376
00:22:11.979 --> 00:22:13.396
Great! I love interviews.

377
00:22:13.563 --> 00:22:16.146
You have to wait. Gale. sorry.
I can't let you in there.

378
00:22:16.313 --> 00:22:19.729
What are you gonna do.
arrest me. Deputy Judy?

379
00:22:19.896 --> 00:22:21.271
If it comes to it.

380
00:22:21.438 --> 00:22:22.813
Civilian interference
with a police investigation

381
00:22:22.979 --> 00:22:24.938
poses many a problem
in a court of law.

382
00:22:25.104 --> 00:22:26.646
OK. listen to me. Judy.

383
00:22:26.813 --> 00:22:28.938
I don't mind that you're
working with my husband

384
00:22:29.104 --> 00:22:32.188
or that you even bake him
those little treats. as you do.

385
00:22:32.354 --> 00:22:34.146
But if you're gonna start acting like him.

386
00:22:34.313 --> 00:22:36.438
you gotta put a moustache on.
"cause you sound ridiculous.

387
00:22:36.604 --> 00:22:37.896
Gale!
Judy!

388
00:22:38.063 --> 00:22:39.479
Gale!

389
00:22:39.646 --> 00:22:42.188
Deputy. Gale.

390
00:22:42.354 --> 00:22:44.146
Please.

391
00:22:44.313 --> 00:22:46.729
Sidney. if you don't mind
giving us a minute.

392
00:22:46.896 --> 00:22:48.854
Sid.
Hi. Gale.

393
00:22:49.021 --> 00:22:52.604
Dewey. would you please
explain to Betty Crocker

394
00:22:52.771 --> 00:22:54.396
that I have every right to be here?

395
00:22:54.563 --> 00:22:56.521
If there"s been another murder
in Woodsboro. obvious...

396
00:22:56.688 --> 00:22:58.063
What?

397
00:22:58.229 --> 00:23:01.313
That is not public information!

398
00:23:01.479 --> 00:23:03.063
It is all over the internet. Dewey!

399
00:23:03.229 --> 00:23:04.604
It is?
Yes!

400
00:23:04.771 --> 00:23:06.854
The whole world knows
about it — before me!

401
00:23:07.021 --> 00:23:09.479
She wants to be a part of
the investigation. Sheriff.

402
00:23:09.646 --> 00:23:12.188
OK. Hang on. Um...

403
00:23:12.354 --> 00:23:17.438
Are you familiar with the phrase
“ wrote the book on this”?

404
00:23:20.354 --> 00:23:22.521
Gale. with all due respect.

405
00:23:22.688 --> 00:23:24.063
I don't see how that pertains...

406
00:23:24.229 --> 00:23:27.813
Because I wrote the book on this!

407
00:23:27.979 --> 00:23:30.688
'The Woodsboro Murders'
by Gale Weathers?

408
00:23:30.854 --> 00:23:33.063
But you're not a reporter any more. Gale.

409
00:23:33.229 --> 00:23:34.729
Whoa. whoa. whoa!
And even if you were...

410
00:23:34.896 --> 00:23:36.771
Don't treat me like I'm the media.

411
00:23:36.938 --> 00:23:40.729
I helped solve these things —
three times. remember?

412
00:23:40.896 --> 00:23:43.021
You and me. together.

413
00:23:43.188 --> 00:23:45.896
But I'm the sheriff now. Gale.

414
00:23:46.063 --> 00:23:48.104
Right.

415
00:23:49.813 --> 00:23:51.729
What. you're not gonna
let me help you with this?

416
00:23:51.896 --> 00:23:53.854
I can't.

417
00:23:55.563 --> 00:23:57.229
Alright. Then I'm going rogue.

418
00:23:58.271 --> 00:23:59.646
This is what I'm good at. Dewey.

419
00:23:59.813 --> 00:24:02.104
This is what I know how to do.

420
00:24:07.771 --> 00:24:10.229
Your lemon squares taste like ass.

421
00:24:12.188 --> 00:24:13.646
They don't.

422
00:24:13.813 --> 00:24:15.188
They really don't.

423
00:24:15.354 --> 00:24:16.729
Thank you. sir.

424
00:24:16.896 --> 00:24:18.271
Veat? Sheriff!

425
00:24:18.438 --> 00:24:20.396
We got a couple of
high school kids in here.

426
00:24:20.563 --> 00:24:23.313
Two of them. they say they got
threatening phone calls this morning

427
00:24:23.479 --> 00:24:24.979
from the victims' phones.

428
00:24:25.146 --> 00:24:28.438
Names are Olivia Morris
and Jill Roberts.

429
00:24:28.604 --> 00:24:30.271
That's Sid's cousin.

430
00:24:30.438 --> 00:24:31.813
Damn.

431
00:24:31.979 --> 00:24:34.188
Right in here. Sheriff.

432
00:24:34.354 --> 00:24:36.313
Hey. Jill.
Sidney!

433
00:24:36.479 --> 00:24:38.646
Hi.
Hi.

434
00:24:38.813 --> 00:24:41.646
It's nice to see you.
even under the circumstances.

435
00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:43.188
You OK?

436
00:24:43.354 --> 00:24:44.229
Yeah.

437
00:24:44.396 --> 00:24:45.854
So. two of you got phone calls?

438
00:24:46.021 --> 00:24:48.729
Yeah. us two.
“What's your favourite scary movie?”

439
00:24:48.896 --> 00:24:52.646
It was the killer's voice — from 'Stab'.

440
00:24:52.813 --> 00:24:55.313
Or. I mean. you know. from your life.

441
00:24:55.479 --> 00:24:57.896
I'm Kirby. by the way. I'm their friend.

442
00:24:58.063 --> 00:25:01.563
And the killer didn't call you?
No.

443
00:25:01.729 --> 00:25:03.771
Is... is that a bad thing?

444
00:25:03.938 --> 00:25:06.604
Does that mean that I'm not gonna live
as long as these two?

445
00:25:06.771 --> 00:25:07.979
No.

446
00:25:08.146 --> 00:25:09.021
Maybe.

447
00:25:09.188 --> 00:25:10.813
Of course not.

448
00:25:10.979 --> 00:25:13.354
Just... just be careful.

449
00:25:13.521 --> 00:25:16.396
Oh. my God! Did you hear that?
I'm gonna be next!

450
00:25:16.563 --> 00:25:18.479
Dewey. I shouldn't be here.
I should leave town.

451
00:25:18.646 --> 00:25:21.354
I'm afraid that's not
really possible. Sidney.

452
00:25:21.521 --> 00:25:24.896
Look. nobody thinks you're involved.
but...“everyone's a suspect”.

453
00:25:25.063 --> 00:25:25.938
I'm sorry.

454
00:25:26.104 --> 00:25:28.896
And there was evidence in your car
connecting the killer to you.

455
00:25:29.063 --> 00:25:30.438
You may be a material witness.

456
00:25:33.188 --> 00:25:36.896
So. look. you'll have
24-hour police protection.

457
00:25:37.063 --> 00:25:38.604
That's comforting.

458
00:25:40.771 --> 00:25:42.604
This is Rebecca.

459
00:25:42.771 --> 00:25:44.896
Oh. my fucking God! Henry!

460
00:25:45.063 --> 00:25:46.771
Yes. it's true!

461
00:25:46.938 --> 00:25:48.729
Two girls. butchered!

462
00:25:48.896 --> 00:25:50.271
Pay day!

463
00:25:50.438 --> 00:25:52.063
I was so not feeling Woodsboro.

464
00:25:52.229 --> 00:25:54.104
I was. like. “Lame PR move.” right?

465
00:25:54.271 --> 00:25:57.604
Well. fuck me. wow!
Best idea ever.

466
00:25:57.771 --> 00:25:59.896
Henry. I'll call you back.

467
00:26:01.771 --> 00:26:03.313
Excuse me...I have to geek out.

468
00:26:03.479 --> 00:26:05.229
I didn't get a chance
to say something earlier.

469
00:26:05.396 --> 00:26:06.896
but it's such an honour to meet you.

470
00:26:07.063 --> 00:26:08.729
Oh. thank you.
Rebecca Walters.

471
00:26:08.896 --> 00:26:12.563
When I was a kid. it was all about
'Top Story with Gale Weathers'.

472
00:26:12.729 --> 00:26:14.313
You were my '90s!

473
00:26:14.479 --> 00:26:17.479
Well. it's Gale Riley now.
You gave it all up for love! I know that.

474
00:26:17.646 --> 00:26:19.438
How long have
you and Dewey been married?

475
00:26:19.604 --> 00:26:22.563
<i>10 years.
Oh! Just like your characters in 'Stab 3!</i>

476
00:26:22.729 --> 00:26:24.771
Woul Wow!

477
00:26:24.938 --> 00:26:26.813
Oh! I didn't mean bad wow.

478
00:26:26.979 --> 00:26:29.604
It just... always seemed like more of
a movie romance than a real one.

479
00:26:29.771 --> 00:26:32.521
because it was a movie. and in real life.
you two would never be...

480
00:26:32.688 --> 00:26:35.396
Ooohh... Dug a hole!

481
00:26:35.563 --> 00:26:36.938
Climbing out... here.

482
00:26:37.104 --> 00:26:40.229
So. anyway. kudos on being brave
enough to drop off the professional map.

483
00:26:40.396 --> 00:26:43.104
Any plans on revitalising
your tarnished brand?

484
00:26:43.271 --> 00:26:44.938
Listen. in about two seconds.

485
00:26:45.104 --> 00:26:48.021
I'm gonna revitalise your face
with my tarnished brand.

486
00:26:50.146 --> 00:26:51.188
I've still got it.

487
00:26:52.729 --> 00:26:54.688
Hmm! Testy.

488
00:27:02.438 --> 00:27:04.646
She's so pretty.

489
00:27:04.813 --> 00:27:06.521
When you think about
what she survived.

490
00:27:06.688 --> 00:27:08.063
she must have scars everywhere.

491
00:27:08.229 --> 00:27:09.688
Shh! Come on.

492
00:27:09.854 --> 00:27:12.021
Her mom was my sister.

493
00:27:12.188 --> 00:27:13.813
I have scars too.

494
00:27:13.979 --> 00:27:16.188
No-one ever asks me about my scars.

495
00:27:16.354 --> 00:27:19.063
I'm sorry. Mrs Roberts.

496
00:27:19.229 --> 00:27:20.604
She means knife scars. Mom.

497
00:27:20.771 --> 00:27:24.479
Oh. Well.. Fine.

498
00:27:27.354 --> 00:27:28.729
How are you?

499
00:27:28.896 --> 00:27:30.438
How's Gale?

500
00:27:31.813 --> 00:27:34.104
I'm alright.

501
00:27:34.271 --> 00:27:37.688
Gale... it's been hard on her.

502
00:27:37.854 --> 00:27:41.729
Small town... small-town husband.

503
00:27:41.896 --> 00:27:44.188
Not much to write about.

504
00:27:46.271 --> 00:27:47.813
You two OK?

505
00:27:49.396 --> 00:27:51.313
Well. I read somewhere once

506
00:27:51.479 --> 00:27:55.021
“'Just when you think things
can't get any worse.

507
00:27:55.188 --> 00:27:56.646
“sometimes they don't.

508
00:27:56.813 --> 00:27:58.813
“Sometimes they get better.”

509
00:27:58.979 --> 00:28:03.021
'Out of Darkness' by Sidney Prescott.
page 220.

510
00:28:12.063 --> 00:28:13.604
I've gotta get going.

511
00:28:19.813 --> 00:28:21.479
It's nice to see you. Dewey.

512
00:28:21.646 --> 00:28:23.396
We've been through a lot together.

513
00:28:23.563 --> 00:28:26.104
And we'll get through this too. OK?

514
00:28:26.271 --> 00:28:28.104
Lock up.
Mm-hm.

515
00:28:47.896 --> 00:28:49.896
Hey. Be cool! It's OK. it's just me.

516
00:28:50.063 --> 00:28:51.771
Relax. relax. It's just me.

517
00:28:51.938 --> 00:28:54.521
What the hell are you doing here?
There are cops right out front!

518
00:28:54.688 --> 00:28:57.021
No match for the ninja. baby.

519
00:28:59.063 --> 00:29:02.021
Anyway. what are you doing
in the house with Sidney Prescott?

520
00:29:02.188 --> 00:29:04.854
<i>That's like being on “Top Chef
with Jeffrey Dahmer.</i>

521
00:29:05.021 --> 00:29:07.479
Look. can you please
get away from the window?

522
00:29:07.646 --> 00:29:10.979
You've no right to be in here.
Not any more.

523
00:29:11.146 --> 00:29:15.063
<i>Hang on. I heard you got
a phone call from the killer.</i>

524
00:29:15.229 --> 00:29:16.979
Is that true?

525
00:29:17.146 --> 00:29:18.729
What do you care?

526
00:29:18.896 --> 00:29:21.813
Don't you think you'd be
a lot safer with me around?

527
00:29:21.979 --> 00:29:24.563
I don't trust you. Trevor.
Hey...

528
00:29:24.729 --> 00:29:27.563
Then I'm just gonna have to
make sure that you do.

529
00:29:27.729 --> 00:29:29.063
Alright?

530
00:29:31.979 --> 00:29:33.604
Oh. sorry. I didn't...

531
00:29:33.771 --> 00:29:36.313
No. he's just leaving. It's my ex.

532
00:29:36.479 --> 00:29:37.646
Oh.

533
00:29:37.813 --> 00:29:39.688
Yeah. Her one and only.

534
00:29:39.854 --> 00:29:41.521
Hi.

535
00:29:41.688 --> 00:29:43.063
Hi.

536
00:29:43.229 --> 00:29:45.771
It's cool to meet you. officially.

537
00:29:45.938 --> 00:29:48.938
I keep meaning to pick up
a copy of your book. but...

538
00:29:50.896 --> 00:29:53.479
You're smaller in person.

539
00:30:00.729 --> 00:30:01.854
What?

540
00:30:02.021 --> 00:30:03.479
Nothing. You just. uh...

541
00:30:03.646 --> 00:30:06.938
You remind me of. uh... me.

542
00:30:09.104 --> 00:30:10.479
Lock your window. OK?

543
00:30:10.646 --> 00:30:12.479
Yeah. Goodnight.

544
00:30:12.646 --> 00:30:14.854
Goodnight.

545
00:30:15.021 --> 00:30:17.771
Sorry about that.

546
00:30:18.979 --> 00:30:21.646
Just making my rounds
before taking off.

547
00:30:21.813 --> 00:30:23.646
Great. Thanks.

548
00:30:26.604 --> 00:30:28.438
You don't remember me. do ya?

549
00:30:28.604 --> 00:30:29.938
Sorry?

550
00:30:30.104 --> 00:30:32.313
We went to high school together.

551
00:30:32.479 --> 00:30:33.729
Judy Hicks.

552
00:30:33.896 --> 00:30:37.563
We had the same home room.
and drama club too.

553
00:30:37.729 --> 00:30:39.688
We were in 'Peter Pan' together.

554
00:30:39.854 --> 00:30:42.104
I played a Lost Boy.

555
00:30:42.271 --> 00:30:46.396
You were... Tiger Lily.

556
00:30:48.729 --> 00:30:51.271
I'm sorry. That was a long time ago.

557
00:30:51.438 --> 00:30:53.854
It's OK. Um...

558
00:30:54.021 --> 00:30:58.354
You had... a lot of stuff
going on back then.

559
00:30:58.521 --> 00:31:01.854
Well. it's nice to see you again. Judy.

560
00:31:02.021 --> 00:31:03.688
You too.

561
00:31:10.313 --> 00:31:11.938
Everything OK upstairs?

562
00:31:12.104 --> 00:31:14.063
You're supposed to be
out front. Perkins.

563
00:31:23.271 --> 00:31:25.938
What's a four-letter word for 'courage'?

564
00:31:26.104 --> 00:31:30.063
Uh...'guts'.

565
00:31:34.979 --> 00:31:37.146
That's Olivia Morris. She lives next door.

566
00:31:37.313 --> 00:31:40.021
She's on the list.
Yeah.

567
00:31:40.188 --> 00:31:42.479
She can live next door to me!

568
00:31:42.646 --> 00:31:45.229
No. seriously. er... Mary.

569
00:31:45.396 --> 00:31:46.771
I'm warning you. OK?

570
00:31:46.938 --> 00:31:48.688
<i>I'm gonna have to get physical.
I mean it.</i>

571
00:31:48.854 --> 00:31:50.813
This is it! Just fuck off!

572
00:32:01.854 --> 00:32:04.354
Hello?
What are you guys up to?

573
00:32:04.521 --> 00:32:06.479
Oh. we're watching 'Shaun of the Dead'.

574
00:32:06.646 --> 00:32:09.229
You know there are two zombies
sitting outside the house in a car?

575
00:32:09.396 --> 00:32:12.313
Yeah. they're cops.
You wanna come up?

576
00:32:12.479 --> 00:32:15.521
Did the Angel of Death leave?
Nah. she's in the guest room.

577
00:32:15.688 --> 00:32:18.979
Forget it. Next door's close enough.

578
00:32:19.146 --> 00:32:20.396
Your mom home?

579
00:32:20.563 --> 00:32:22.563
She's at her boyfriend's.

580
00:32:22.729 --> 00:32:24.438
It's creepy around here tonight.

581
00:32:24.604 --> 00:32:29.396
Well. the zombies are still in their car.
so you should be alright.

582
00:32:29.563 --> 00:32:30.938
Call me tomorrow. OK?

583
00:32:31.104 --> 00:32:32.521
OK.

584
00:32:32.688 --> 00:32:34.188
She didn't wanna come up?

585
00:32:34.354 --> 00:32:35.813
She fears the reaper.

586
00:32:35.979 --> 00:32:37.604
Watch this.

587
00:32:46.604 --> 00:32:47.979
Speaking.

588
00:32:48.146 --> 00:32:52.188
What's your favourite
scary movie. Olivia?

589
00:32:52.354 --> 00:32:54.313
That was the worst imitation
I've ever heard. Jill.

590
00:32:54.479 --> 00:32:56.813
Speaking of 'Stab'. you hear
where the Stab-a-thon's gonna be yet?

591
00:32:56.979 --> 00:32:59.271
No. It doesn't matter to me anyways.

592
00:32:59.438 --> 00:33:00.938
My mom doesn't let me go.

593
00:33:03.771 --> 00:33:05.854
It's Trevor. I'll handle this.

594
00:33:06.021 --> 00:33:08.104
Trevor's calling.
Again.

595
00:33:08.271 --> 00:33:09.646
What do you want?

596
00:33:09.813 --> 00:33:11.563
I wanna talk to Jill.

597
00:33:11.729 --> 00:33:14.271
Uh. no. it's Kirby. Sorry. Trevor.

598
00:33:14.438 --> 00:33:17.104
Jill is screening her calls
from all past relationships.

599
00:33:17.271 --> 00:33:18.771
What's going on over there?

600
00:33:18.938 --> 00:33:20.479
Hang on a sec. What is he saying?

601
00:33:20.646 --> 00:33:22.396
I'm not Trevor.

602
00:33:22.563 --> 00:33:24.063
What?

603
00:33:24.229 --> 00:33:25.604
I can barely hear you. Trevor.

604
00:33:25.771 --> 00:33:28.188
This isn't Trevor.

605
00:33:28.354 --> 00:33:33.104
Oh. Oh. alright. Well. then why do you
have his phone. whoever this is?

606
00:33:33.271 --> 00:33:35.188
He's trying
to do Ghostface!

607
00:33:35.354 --> 00:33:37.646
He's being weird.

608
00:33:37.813 --> 00:33:39.729
I wanna talk to Jill.

609
00:33:39.896 --> 00:33:41.896
OK. well. she doesn't wanna talk to you.

610
00:33:42.063 --> 00:33:44.604
Come on. Mr Ghostface. Whisper to me.

611
00:33:44.771 --> 00:33:47.188
Aren't you supposed to
ask me a question?

612
00:33:47.354 --> 00:33:49.021
Alright.

613
00:33:49.188 --> 00:33:51.521
<i>How's the movie?
What movie?</i>

614
00:33:51.688 --> 00:33:53.229
'Shaun of the Dead'.

615
00:33:55.146 --> 00:33:56.604
How did you know that?

616
00:33:56.771 --> 00:34:00.146
Because I'm standing in the closet.

617
00:34:00.313 --> 00:34:02.021
Stop. You are not.

618
00:34:02.188 --> 00:34:04.563
What's going on?
Trevor's being weird.

619
00:34:04.729 --> 00:34:06.729
I mean. if it is him. I don't know.
What?

620
00:34:06.896 --> 00:34:10.396
This is not fucking Trevor!
Well. then who the fuck are you?

621
00:34:10.563 --> 00:34:13.188
Open the closet door.

622
00:34:15.521 --> 00:34:18.188
You do know there are cops
all over this house.

623
00:34:18.354 --> 00:34:21.021
I think I'd have just enough time
to slice someone open!

624
00:34:22.646 --> 00:34:24.813
I'll talk to him.
Shh.

625
00:34:26.271 --> 00:34:28.521
What's going on over there. you guys?

626
00:34:28.688 --> 00:34:30.063
Sorry. I don't know.

627
00:34:30.229 --> 00:34:31.604
Kirby...
Shh!

628
00:34:31.771 --> 00:34:34.688
- Kirby...
- Come on. Do it!

629
00:34:34.854 --> 00:34:36.854
There is no way you're in there.

630
00:34:37.021 --> 00:34:38.896
See for yourself!

631
00:34:39.063 --> 00:34:40.979
Kirby...

632
00:34:41.146 --> 00:34:44.063
Kirby. come on. Talk to me.
This isn't funny!

633
00:34:44.229 --> 00:34:45.438
Kirby!

634
00:34:52.729 --> 00:34:55.563
Liar. I'm over this.

635
00:34:55.729 --> 00:34:57.938
I never said I was in your closet.

636
00:35:03.771 --> 00:35:05.146
Oh. my God!

637
00:35:05.313 --> 00:35:06.646
Olivia!

638
00:35:14.104 --> 00:35:15.229
Stop!

639
00:35:20.896 --> 00:35:22.521
No! Help!

640
00:35:23.563 --> 00:35:25.604
No! Don't!

641
00:35:37.646 --> 00:35:39.313
- Hoss!
- Somebody help!

642
00:35:39.479 --> 00:35:40.813
Perkins!

643
00:35:42.146 --> 00:35:43.271
Shit!

644
00:36:39.229 --> 00:36:41.396
- What?
- Welcome home. Sidney.

645
00:36:41.563 --> 00:36:43.521
Preview of coming events.

646
00:36:43.688 --> 00:36:46.021
Why don't you come for me?
You got the balls for that?

647
00:36:46.188 --> 00:36:50.521
Oh. poor Sidney. You think this is all
about you. You think you're still the star.

648
00:36:50.688 --> 00:36:52.479
This isn't a fucking movie!
It will be.

649
00:36:52.646 --> 00:36:55.271
These are innocent people.
Spare me the lecture!

650
00:36:55.438 --> 00:36:57.813
You've done very well by
all this bloodshed. haven't you?

651
00:36:57.979 --> 00:37:00.021
Well. how about the town you left behind?

652
00:37:00.188 --> 00:37:02.021
I've got plans for you.

653
00:37:02.188 --> 00:37:06.563
I"m gonna slit your eyelids in half so you
don't blink when I stab you in the face.

654
00:37:06.729 --> 00:37:10.563
You'll die when I want you to. Sidney.
not a moment before.

655
00:37:10.729 --> 00:37:15.146
Until then. you're going to suffer.

656
00:37:15.313 --> 00:37:17.271
Sidney?
Jill?

657
00:37:17.438 --> 00:37:19.063
Stay right there!

658
00:37:19.229 --> 00:37:20.313
Is she...

659
00:37:20.479 --> 00:37:22.521
Do not look. OK?

660
00:37:22.688 --> 00:37:24.771
She said you were the angel of death.

661
00:37:24.938 --> 00:37:26.979
Look out!

662
00:37:48.438 --> 00:37:49.813
What's going on in here?

663
00:37:49.979 --> 00:37:51.563
He's in here.

664
00:37:51.729 --> 00:37:53.229
Where is he?

665
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:55.563
Ma'am?

666
00:37:55.729 --> 00:37:57.021
He was.

667
00:37:58.521 --> 00:37:59.979
We'll go check out back.

668
00:38:00.146 --> 00:38:01.146
Jill?

669
00:38:01.313 --> 00:38:03.063
Don't.

670
00:38:12.313 --> 00:38:13.771
What happened?

671
00:38:13.938 --> 00:38:15.979
Oh. my God. Jill!

672
00:38:17.563 --> 00:38:19.521
Jesus! Hey. I'm here.

673
00:38:19.688 --> 00:38:21.188
Hey. baby. I'm here.
Come on. let's go.

674
00:38:21.354 --> 00:38:23.063
Let's go. Let's get through it. alright?

675
00:38:23.229 --> 00:38:25.646
Jill?

676
00:38:25.813 --> 00:38:27.021
Oh. my God!

677
00:38:27.188 --> 00:38:29.063
Are you OK? Keep pressure on it.

678
00:38:29.229 --> 00:38:31.021
There's nobody back there.

679
00:38:31.188 --> 00:38:33.854
- Hoss. call it in.
- Right.

680
00:38:34.021 --> 00:38:37.021
Hey... are you OK?

681
00:38:37.188 --> 00:38:40.396
You should look upstairs.

682
00:38:57.646 --> 00:38:59.979
The kids are over there.
Over by that tree.

683
00:39:00.146 --> 00:39:02.021
It's all your fault. Sidney!

684
00:39:02.188 --> 00:39:04.146
You're just like your mother!

685
00:39:04.313 --> 00:39:06.854
Hoss. clear these people out.

686
00:39:07.021 --> 00:39:09.896
- I thought this was over!
- Come on. Leave her alone.

687
00:39:14.438 --> 00:39:16.229
I'm sorry about what I said.

688
00:39:18.146 --> 00:39:19.646
Do you wanna go get that looked at?

689
00:39:19.813 --> 00:39:21.646
Yeah.

690
00:39:23.854 --> 00:39:25.479
What the hell happened?

691
00:39:25.646 --> 00:39:29.521
OK. I saw him go into that yard.
two houses down. right before.

692
00:39:29.688 --> 00:39:31.604
And I circled around to cut him off.

693
00:39:31.771 --> 00:39:32.854
And?

694
00:39:33.021 --> 00:39:35.813
And I met Hoss coming
from the other direction.

695
00:39:35.979 --> 00:39:38.313
He must have circled back around
somehow. He's like a ghost.

696
00:39:38.479 --> 00:39:41.854
Chief. we're sorry.
I feel terrible.

697
00:39:42.021 --> 00:39:43.396
Alright.

698
00:39:43.563 --> 00:39:45.104
Get outta here.

699
00:39:59.188 --> 00:40:02.938
This is 'Hall Pass' with Robbie Mercer.
webcasting live in our darkest hour.

700
00:40:03.104 --> 00:40:06.479
What began as a day of remembrance
has ended with serial murder.

701
00:40:06.646 --> 00:40:10.188
Olivia Morris. who officially
will never go out with me. is dead.

702
00:40:10.354 --> 00:40:12.438
So is Jenny Randall and Marnie Cooper.

703
00:40:12.604 --> 00:40:16.479
Our local legacy. the 'Stab' movies.
is coming to life.

704
00:40:16.646 --> 00:40:19.313
Excuse me. Are you
recording with that thing?

705
00:40:19.479 --> 00:40:22.146
Live video blog upload.
He's webcasting right now.

706
00:40:22.313 --> 00:40:24.563
Ah. Mind turning it off
for a little old school off-the-record?

707
00:40:24.729 --> 00:40:26.563
Can't. Owe it to my audience.

708
00:40:26.729 --> 00:40:28.771
Turn that fucking thing off.

709
00:40:28.938 --> 00:40:30.479
OK.

710
00:40:31.521 --> 00:40:35.396
So. you two are the boys that run
the movie club at Woodsboro High. huh?

711
00:40:35.563 --> 00:40:38.604
Charlie runs it. I'm just VP
in case he takes a bullet.

712
00:40:38.771 --> 00:40:40.146
It's called Cinema Club.

713
00:40:40.313 --> 00:40:44.104
So you must have a very unique insight
into the movie buffs at your school.

714
00:40:45.271 --> 00:40:46.938
Maybe.

715
00:40:47.104 --> 00:40:49.396
What if we could catch the killer

716
00:40:49.563 --> 00:40:51.563
by working together?

717
00:40:51.729 --> 00:40:53.813
Two generations
of cutting-edge journalists

718
00:40:53.979 --> 00:40:56.896
intertwining our passions for media.

719
00:40:57.063 --> 00:40:58.896
What would you say?

720
00:40:59.063 --> 00:41:00.438
I love you.

721
00:41:00.604 --> 00:41:01.979
Very good.

722
00:41:02.146 --> 00:41:06.396
Now. you give me your expertise on
the gore geek scene at Woodsboro High

723
00:41:06.563 --> 00:41:08.563
and maybe I give you
something in return...

724
00:41:08.729 --> 00:41:12.104
say a celebrity visit
to your Cinema Club

725
00:41:12.271 --> 00:41:13.813
by me?

726
00:41:15.563 --> 00:41:16.979
What about Sidney?

727
00:41:17.146 --> 00:41:19.896
What about Sidney?
Yeah. you know her. right?

728
00:41:20.063 --> 00:41:22.063
I mean. you're friends with her.

729
00:41:22.229 --> 00:41:25.021
No of fence. but that'd be
a big deal for Cinema Club.

730
00:41:25.188 --> 00:41:27.854
A visit from Sidney Prescott?
I mean. she's the star!

731
00:41:28.021 --> 00:41:29.396
Ohh!

732
00:41:29.563 --> 00:41:32.354
Yeah. she's Daniel Radcliffe
to my J.K. Rowling.

733
00:41:32.521 --> 00:41:34.938
Well. without the book sales
and the box office.

734
00:41:35.104 --> 00:41:36.646
Whatever.

735
00:41:40.063 --> 00:41:43.354
There's no broken bones.
I think you'll be fine. Take it easy.

736
00:41:43.521 --> 00:41:45.396
You're lucky. Sidney.

737
00:41:48.271 --> 00:41:50.313
So. Sidney... Ooh! Ow.

738
00:41:50.479 --> 00:41:55.021
Anyway. long story short. Random wants
to lock you into three more books now.

739
00:41:55.188 --> 00:41:58.563
See the blank line in your contract?
You can name your price.

740
00:41:58.729 --> 00:42:00.479
And as soon as you're clear
in this investigation.

741
00:42:00.646 --> 00:42:02.146
we're on the next plane to New York.

742
00:42:02.313 --> 00:42:05.563
I've booked 'Today'. 'The View'.
'Nancy Grace'. 'MTV News'...

743
00:42:05.729 --> 00:42:08.146
Excuse me — can I ask you a question?
Mmm!

744
00:42:08.313 --> 00:42:10.188
Did you read my book?

745
00:42:10.354 --> 00:42:13.188
Thought I'd wait for the movie.

746
00:42:13.354 --> 00:42:15.188
Book tour's over.

747
00:42:15.354 --> 00:42:17.271
Sidney!

748
00:42:17.438 --> 00:42:19.521
Accept your situation.

749
00:42:19.688 --> 00:42:21.854
You're a victim for life.

750
00:42:22.021 --> 00:42:24.979
So embrace it. Use it.

751
00:42:25.146 --> 00:42:28.188
I know you care about your readers —
all those little downtrodden fucks

752
00:42:28.354 --> 00:42:31.938
that just need a light at the end of their tunnel
so they don't jump off a bridge.

753
00:42:32.104 --> 00:42:36.604
And a lucky break like this. I'm talking
100% increase in sales minimum.

754
00:42:36.771 --> 00:42:39.063
That's maybe a million more people
get your message.

755
00:42:39.229 --> 00:42:40.604
and you get a ton more cheques.

756
00:42:40.771 --> 00:42:41.646
Win-win.

757
00:42:41.813 --> 00:42:45.479
I won"t be
needing you any more.

758
00:42:45.646 --> 00:42:47.563
Sidney!
You're fired.

759
00:42:47.729 --> 00:42:49.771
Fired?
Fired.

760
00:42:49.938 --> 00:42:52.021
Fine.

761
00:43:13.729 --> 00:43:16.521
“Have you even read
my book. Rebecca?”

762
00:43:29.854 --> 00:43:32.271
The problem with Sidney
is that she never gets laid.

763
00:43:32.438 --> 00:43:34.396
or even a little shit-faced
once in a while.

764
00:43:34.563 --> 00:43:37.646
She'll call me tonight and apologise.

765
00:43:37.813 --> 00:43:39.438
Just watch.

